  "_comment": "Coverage thresholds are conservative ratchets over shipping DotBoxD assemblies (src/) using merged Cobertura reports from the Kernels and Services coverage suites. Measured local baseline on 2026-07-05: global line 85.15%, global branch 77.80%; area baselines are intentionally rounded down so normal noise does not fail unrelated PRs. Raise thresholds toward the current values as tests improve."
